First Lady Melania Trump gave a speech in the East Room of the White House addressing the opioid epidemic in the United States. She thanked those in attendance for sharing their stories and discussed the impact of addiction on children. Melania expressed her interest in helping to fight the epidemic and shared what she has learned from those affected by it. She emphasized the importance of normalizing the stigma around drug addiction and educating children and parents. Melania also acknowledged the efforts of recovery centers like Lily's Place in West Virginia and expressed her support for her husband's administration's commitment to combating the crisis. She concluded by calling for citizens to join forces in ending the health crisis.